text.section:
Unless the articles of merger preclude the right to abandon the merger or permit some other vote or manner of abandonment, a proposed merger may be abandoned before the effective date of the articles by:
A majority vote of the partners of a partnership party to the articles;
Unanimous consent of the members of a limited liability company party to the articles;
A majority vote of the general partners and a majority in interest of the limited partners, as defined in § 10-208 of this article, of any limited partnership party to the articles;
A majority vote of the entire board of directors of a corporation party to the articles; and
A majority vote of the entire board of trustees of a business trust party to the articles.
